INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jor3200','letter','1780-06-20','Philadelphia','PA','US','Joseph','Reed','','George','Washington','','individual','','I have received your favor of the 16th instant, directing the march of the city light-horse, for which the necessary orders will be given, and they will proceed with all possible despatch.','ltr_jor3200.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jor3201','letter','1779-11-24','Philadelphia','PA','US','Joseph','Reed','','George','Washington','','individual','','we never exhibited any other charge against General Arnold to Congress, than that of appropriating the public wagons of the State to private uses','ltr_jor3201.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jor3202','letter','1779-07-14','Philadelphia','PA','US','Joseph','Reed','','George','Washington','','individual','','though it was and is the universal opinion, that the number of men under General Sullivan is greater than can be fed, when he proceeds a little further on the expedition, yet we gave early and peremptory orders to the companies of rangers to join him','ltr_jor3202.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jor3203','letter','1780-06-05','Philadelphia','PA','US','Joseph','Reed','','George','Washington','','individual','','I do not know by what means the expected assistance from France has been procured; but it will certainly give a complexion to the alliance in future, according to the reception it meets with here.','ltr_jor3203.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853');
